sec.p:
A 59‐year‐old woman presented to our attention because of her routine oncologic follow‐up after a treated oral cancer. Informed consent was obtained to perform an MRI examination. The MRI imaging protocol was obtained with a 1.5 T Siemens device and included the following sequences:
Axial T1‐weighted, with 3.5 mm slice thickness;
Axial T2‐weighted, with 3.5 mm slice thickness;
Axial T2 TIRM, with 3.5 mm slice thickness;
Coronal T2 TIRM, with 3.5 mm slice thickness;
Sagittal T2‐weighted, with 2.0 mm slice thickness;
Axial DWI, with 3.5 mm slice thickness;
T1 VIBE FAT SAT three‐dimensional without and with contrast, with 1.0 mm slice thickness.
